Always write everything in English:

## Code and Comments
- Write all code comments in English
- Use English variable names, function names, and class names
- Write error messages in English
- Use English for console.log statements and debugging output

## Documentation
- Write README files in English
- Write API documentation in English
- Write inline documentation in English
- Write commit messages in English

## User Interface
- Write all user-facing text in English
- Use English for button labels, form fields, and navigation
- Write error messages displayed to users in English
- Use English for tooltips and help text

## Configuration Files
- Write package.json descriptions in English
- Use English for configuration comments
- Write environment variable descriptions in English

## Examples

✅ Good:
```typescript
// Calculate user score based on activity
function calculateUserScore(userActivity: UserActivity): number {
  const baseScore = 100;
  const activityMultiplier = userActivity.points / 10;
  return baseScore * activityMultiplier;
}

// Error handling for invalid input
if (!userInput) {
  throw new Error("User input is required");
}
```

❌ Bad:
```typescript
// Kullanıcı skorunu hesapla
function kullaniciSkoruHesapla(kullaniciAktivitesi: KullaniciAktivitesi): number {
  const temelSkor = 100;
  const aktiviteCarpani = kullaniciAktivitesi.puanlar / 10;
  return temelSkor * aktiviteCarpani;
}

// Hatalı giriş kontrolü
if (!kullaniciGirisi) {
  throw new Error("Kullanıcı girişi gerekli");
}
```

## Package.json Example

✅ Good:
```json
{
  "name": "my-project",
  "description": "A modern web application built with Next.js and TypeScript",
  "scripts": {
    "dev": "Start development server",
    "build": "Build for production",
    "test": "Run test suite"
  }
}
```

❌ Bad:
```json
{
  "name": "proje-adi",
  "description": "Next.js ve TypeScript ile geliştirilmiş modern web uygulaması",
  "scripts": {
    "dev": "Geliştirme sunucusunu başlat",
    "build": "Üretim için derle",
    "test": "Testleri çalıştır"
  }
}
```

Remember: All code, documentation, comments, and user-facing text must be written in English for consistency and international collaboration.
